  "prompt": "What can I do to save my laptop battery while downloading?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to save your laptop battery while downloading:\n\n1. Lower screen brightness\n- Reduces power consumption significantly\n\n2. Close unnecessary background applications\n- Frees up system resources and reduces battery drain\n\n3. Use power-saving mode\n- Limits CPU performance and reduces power usage\n\n4. Disable Wi-Fi/Bluetooth when not in use\n- Prevents additional power consumption\n\n5. Plug in your laptop if possible\n- Direct power source is always best during downloads\n\n6. Use a wired internet connection\n- Wi-Fi typically uses more battery than ethernet\n\n7. Choose download times strategically\n- Download during charging or when plugged in\n\n8. Pause other intensive tasks\n- Avoid running multiple heavy processes simultaneously\n\n9. Update device drivers\n- Can improve battery efficiency\n\n10. Consider battery-saving browser extensions\n- Some extensions can help manage download processes\n\nBonus tip: If you're using a laptop with removable battery, consider using an external power bank for long downloads.",
